I usually don't write any reviews, but couldn't resist after I saw a the last review by Kirill Kanevsky who was there the same time we were. He actually closed the door twice after the staff had explained to him that the policy is to keep the door open. I do admit it was chilly outside, but the restaurant was nice enough to close the door half way to try to accommodate him even though multiple people inside were not comfortable dinning inside with the door closed. I just hate to see people write negative reviews which are uncalled for especially when the restaurant tried to do everything to accommodate him, and he had no consideration for anything but his own preference and also being non compliant.

I've lived in sunny isles for 3 years now, I've come to this place over 50 times, and I never have an issue. The other day I went there after a long day of work, and the server Antoinette told me the kitchen closes at 9:30pm. I told her okay can we order or is it to late she said no we can order. So I simply asked for a lomo saltado extra sauce, because I really enjoy sauce. She then said no it comes the way it comes, I told her I've ordered this dish multiple times and never have an issue. She said well it comes on a big dish, and it comes out the way it does. I manage restaurants for a living, literally 5 star restaurants and never have I ever denied a request so simple. Not only that, but the way she handled and spoke to me was extremely rude. I really think you need to retrain her how to deal with guest. We are the ones that keeps you open. I ended up going to Cvi.Che 105 in Aventura, and they took care of the order without a question. So yeah I won't be going back ever again, and I won't recommend this restaurant to anyone of my guest like I've done over 100 times. So thank you Antoinette for your horrible service.

I went in for breakfast.  It was raining and I was the only person in the restaurant.  There were two servers and I still managed to get horrible service. I ordered the breakfast special.  The eggs were so overcooked that I had to use a knife to get through them, the bacon was so overdone it shattered in my mouth. I got a piece and a half of toast, I wonder what they did with the other half.  My coffee was never refilled and both servers just spent the whole time joking with each other behind the counter. When the bill came there was auto gratuity added already. No wonder they don't do any work if they're getting tipped for their (non existant) service anyway. I've served for 10+ years and have never given service this poor, especially with an empty restaurant.  And to still get a tip for your exceptionally poor service? Unbelievable. Needless to say I will not be back, nor will anyone I know if I have a say in it.
